5. RELATED FINDINGS (12mo_250k run, 25/10/65 split)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  • With target ≥75% sensitivity and ≥65% specificity, and calibration on the
    validation set, the recommended model is Ensemble (Top 2) at threshold 0.015,
    achieving 80.62% test sensitivity and 64.83% specificity (target_met = True).
  • Single-model best for 75/65: XGBoost @ 0.015 (80.03% sens, 65.26% spec) and
    CatBoost @ 0.020 (78.06% sens, 68.25% spec). Ensemble (Top 2) gives the
    highest test sensitivity among options meeting the target.
  • Test AUC is strong: Ensemble (Top 2) 0.8160, XGBoost 0.8143, CatBoost 0.8140.
    The 250k cohort has low cancer prevalence (~2.7%); PPV at target is ~6%,
    NPV remains high (99.18%).
  • Top predictive features (XGBoost and SHAP): alcohol recording (units, unique
    terms), eGFR (range, trend, max, pct change), haemoglobin (min, median,
    first), BMI (IQR, WA count), age–smoking and overall suspicion score.
  • Overfitting: train–val AUC gaps are moderate for main trees; val–test gaps
    are small. Threshold and metrics use calibrated probabilities for 75/65.


